	9. SUBSEQUENT EVENTS









	 


	In accordance with ASC 855-10, the Company has analyzed its operations subsequent to February 28, 2017 to the date these financial statements were issued, and has determined that it does not have any material subsequent events to disclose, except as noted below.


	 


	On February 6, 2017, Blake Insomnia Therapeutics Inc. and Sajo Consulting LLC announced entry into a Letter of Intent to provide certain services related to development and commercialization of Zleepax™, in combination with formulations to produce a series of oral drug products to aid in the treatment of insomnia. This venture looks to accelerate develop of a product to treat transient insomnia through the mechanism of Blake’s proprietary formula.


	 









	 




